      <section eId="sec_13_A_3_4">
        <num>13-A-3.4</num>
        <heading>Disclosure of other digital assets of principal</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_13_A_3_4__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>a written request for disclosure in physical or electronic form;\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_13_A_3_4__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>a copy of the power of attorney that gives the agent specific\nauthority over digital assets or general authority to act on behalf of\nthe principal;\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_13_A_3_4__subsec_c">
          <num>(c)</num>
          <content>
            <p>an affidavit in which the affiant attests that the copy is an\naccurate copy of the original power of attorney and that, to the best of\nthe affiant's knowledge, the power remains in effect; and\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_13_A_3_4__subsec_d">
          <num>(d)</num>
          <content>
            <p>if requested by the custodian:\n</p>
          </content>
          <paragraph eId="sec_13_A_3_4__subsec_d__subsec_1">
            <num>(1)</num>
            <content>
              <p>a number, username, address, or other unique subscriber or account\nidentifier assigned by the custodian to identify the principal's\naccount; or\n</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="sec_13_A_3_4__subsec_d__subsec_2">
            <num>(2)</num>
            <content>
              <p>evidence linking the account to the principal.\n</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
        </subsection>
      </section>
